<TITLE> RAB files cases against two for porn films, drugs </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com) - Police Monday filed two cases against Mushfiqur Rahman Tomal and his friend Mahmud Al Juberi Shanon for making pornographic films. The two were found to have Yaba, a drug, in their possessionthe reason for their arrest, according to the cases filed with Gulshan Police Station. RAB deputy assistant director AHM Humayun Kabir filed the case against Tomal while another RAB officer, Abdur Rashid Sarker, filed the case against Shanon. Gulshan police sub-inspector Gulshan Ara Begum said to bdnews24.com that Tomal and Juberi were arrested along with their friends Ahmed Shafique, Dai Khan Bir Chinu, Salman Rahim Joarder and Altaf Akmal Kollol in Gulshan and Banani Wednesday. The arrested youths had Yaba tablets in their possession. According to case details, Tomal had acted in several porn films and made young women take drugs and take part in the sex films. RAB officials said they filed the case because they were convinced the films were shot with secret cameras. Several porn CDs were seized from Shanon, the RAB officers alleged. RAB said the six arrested youths have been taken into remand for interrogation. bdnews24.com
